The Core Design Philosophy
I would make one principle non-negotiable because it solves the coordination problems you originally described:
Everything in KPM is contextual and traceable.
A feature is never just a card on a board. It is the center of collaboration. From a single feature, a team member or manager should be able to access:
The business requirements.
Related product module and roadmap milestone.
Assigned team members and responsibilities.
Design files (e.g., Figma).
API specifications and documentation.
GitHub repository, branches, commits, and pull requests.
Sprint assignment and progress.
Daily updates related to the feature.
Meetings where it was discussed.
Decisions and action items.
Review history and approvals.
QA results and bugs.
Deployment status and release version.

